                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 5, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Does your No. 7, March 4, 5 p.m. mean that it is not possible to put up a bond
                    instead of depositing securities or cash? The bank is <pb facs="0547" n="467"
                        xml:id="pg_467"/> very anxious to exhaust all possibilities along this line.
                    Please reply by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
